<p>Which means that it works but it is sealed, letâ€™s unseal it.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Enter the container with the command
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="rouge-gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
</pre></td><td class="rouge-code"><pre>docker exec -it vault bash
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Run <code class="highlighter-rouge">vault unseal</code></li>
  <li>It is going to ask for a key, you can pass any of the keys it provided to you before, for each time you need to run <code class="highlighter-rouge">vault unseal</code>, you need to do it 3 times.</li>
</ol>

<p>After the third one you will see the response:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="rouge-gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
2
3
